This paper deals with learning abductive reasoning from examples, which is a task that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of declarative background knowledge, which is a topic that is often studied in natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of graphical causal models is another aspect of the paper that is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the exception-tolerant setting, which is a topic that is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
